1: Gap #1¶

Can we train a classifier to correctly classify the following actions within a possession of ShotTracker data? (http://developer.shottracker.com/#stats-stats-possessions-get for API reference):

  • On-ball screen
  • UCLA screen
  • Pin-down screen
  • Flare screen
  • Backdoor cut
  • Rubcut/handoff

2: Gap #2¶

Is there a relationship between the actions that happen in a possession and the outcome?

Goal: regression with points, rebounds, etc.

  • Does this analysis allow us to generalize to the whole game of basketball? (tougher question to answer)
  • Using coaching literature, we might be able to say stuff about this relationship in the college game

mypossession = 1582588196315
s = 'http://api.shottracker.com/v1/data/sensors/locations/possessions/'+str(mypossession)+'?team_id=1930'
p = shottracker_request(path=s.replace('http://api.shottracker.com',''))
myframes = []
for location in p.json().get('locations'):
        myframes.append(pd.DataFrame(json.loads(json.dumps(location.get('placements')))))
        
fig = plt.figure(figsize = (12,10))
ims = []
for frame in myframes:
    players = frame.loc[frame['type'] == 'PLAYER']
    balls = frame.loc[frame['type'] == 'BALL']
    im = plt.scatter(players['x'],players['y'],color='blue',marker = 'o',linewidth=8)
    im2 = plt.scatter(balls['x'],balls['y'],color ='orange',marker = 'o',linewidth=10)
    im3 = plt.scatter(balls['x'],balls['y'],s = 130, color ='black',marker = 'x',linewidth=1)
    im4 = plt.scatter(balls['x'],balls['y'],s = 150, color ='black',marker = '+',linewidth=1)
    _ = ims.append([im,im2,im3,im4])
ani = ArtistAnimation(fig, ims, interval = 250, repeat_delay = 1000, blit=True);

from IPython.display import HTML
HTML(ani.to_jshtml())

The goal of the classifier is to learn the relationship between the xy-datapoints and these actions.

Currently, the following are used for classification:

  • ANN
  • SVM
  • RNN with LSTM layers

Based on the lit review, CNNs might be a good idea to try
